title: wish_for_blooming_together
body:
A limited-time event in [[Link! Like! Love Live!]].

[[Hinoshita Kaho]] asks for help from everyone to petition the Love Live! management to allow [[Ceras Yanagida Lilienfeld]], a third-year in middle school, to participate in the Love Live! playoffs as one of Mizukawa's school idols, so her dream can come true, because Mizukawa High School is closing down come the next school year.

The petition succeeded, and Ceras was allowed to participate alongside [[Katsuragi Izumi]] as Edel Note.

title: chengdu_j-36
body:
The [b]"Chengdu J-36"[/b] is a placeholder designation given to a Chinese prototype stealth [[fighter jet]] developed for the [[People's Liberation Army Air Force]]. The aircraft made its first public appearance on 26 December 2024, coinciding with the birthday of [[Mao Zedong]].

The aircraft is very unusual in design, being a tailless flying delta wing trijet. It is speculated to be a part of the development program for the sixth-generation fighter for the PLAAF.

title: ore_no_imouto_ga_konna_ni_kawaii_wake_ga_nai
body:
[b]Ore no Imouto ga Konna ni Kawaii Wake ga Nai[/b] (俺の妹がこんなに可愛いわけがない, lit. [i]My Little Sister Can't Be This Cute[/i], abbrev. [i]OreImo[/i]) is a light novel series written by Fushimi Tsukasa, with illustrations by [[Kanzaki Hiro]]. Also adapted into a 2009 manga, with illustrations by [[Ikeda Sakura]], and a 2010 anime.

For years, 17-year-old [[Kousaka Kyousuke]] and his 14-year-old sister [[kousaka_kirino|Kirino]] rarely, if ever, talked to each other, until the day Kyousuke picks up a mahou-shoujo anime DVD case Kirino dropped, only to find out that it actually contains a little sister incest H-game. The ensuing chain of events finally force the siblings to have their first serious conversation in years.

h4. Characters

title: jing_yuan
body:
A [i][[Honkai: Star Rail]][/i] character. 

One of the seven generals of the Xianzhou Alliance's Cloud Knights and one of the Six Charioteers of the Luofu. Voiced by [[Ono Daisuke]] (JP) and [[Cy Yu|Alejandro Saab]] (EN).

He is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[grey hair]] tied to a [[ponytail]], and [[yellow eyes]]. His outfit consists of a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[white shirt]] worn with [[shoulder armor]] and [[pauldrons]], [[black belt]], [[red pants]], [[black footwear|black]] [[boots]], and a [[red ribbon|red]] [[hair ribbon]] tying his ponytail.

h4. Appearance

* !post #7690439: Base art
* !post #8768157: Before Dawn (signature Light Cone)

h4. Profile
[expand]
Although his appearance may be one of indolence, the Cloud Knight general who commands the Xianzhou Luofu is more meticulous than seemingly meets the eye.

He does not consider saving a situation from the brink of disaster to be a show of wisdom, and is thus fastidious with routine affairs to avoid any potential problems.

Due to his careful management, the Xianzhou have enjoyed many years of peace, with Jing Yuan's seemingly lazy demeanor having earned him the moniker of "Dozing General."
[/expand]

title: battle_mage_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[Female Mage_(dungeon_and_fighter)|]]. Also known as the Bellatrix or Astarte.

Her default appearance has high-set twintails, while her outfit consists of a short black jacket, red dress vest, black shorts, and jewelled gauntlets.

As an Astarte, her hair is generally longer and she wears a black and red one-piece with a long skirt and black shorts.

As a Neo Battle Mage, she wears fancier robes with gold trim and black thighhighs. Her older alter ego, an avatar of the goddess Teana, is reflected underneath her.

In all of her official appearances, she wields a spear of some variety, her weapon of choice.

h4. Appearance

* !asset #24660957: Default
* !asset #24660956: Astarte
* !asset #24660959: Neo Battle Mage

title: sparkle_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
Playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]] and in [[Honkai Impact 3rd]] (via crossover event). 

A Masked Fool who follows Aha, the Aeon of Elation. Goes by the name "Hanabi" ("Firework") in Japanese. Voiced by [[Ueda Reina]] (JP) and [[Lizzie Freeman]] (EN). 

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] tied into [[twintails]], [[pink eyes]] with [[butterfly-shaped pupils]], [[small breasts|small]]/[[medium breasts]], and [[facial mark]]s under her eyes. Her default outfit is [[Japanese clothes|Japanese-themed]] and comprises a [[black choker]] with a [[jingle bell]], [[red dress]] with [[detached sleeves]], dark purple [[obi]], [[black gloves]], [[red footwear|red]] [[sandals]], and a [[fox mask]].

title: demonic_lancer
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/3/30/Demon_Lancer_Full_Body.jpg] is a young man with dark purple hair and red eyes, wearing a gray jacket with fur trim, gray dress vest with white shirt, gray pants, and black gauntlets and greaves.

Subclasses:
* [[vanguard_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Vanguard]] (Revenant, Warlord)
* [[skirmisher (dungeon and fighter)|Skirmisher]] (Highlander, Durandal)
* [[impaler (dungeon and fighter)|Impaler]] (Abbadon, Erebus)

title: impaler_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[demonic_lancer|Demonic Lancer]]. Also known as the Abbadon or Erebus.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/e/e2/Dark_Lancer_Art.png] has his hair parted down the middle, and a predominantly black version of his base class's outfit, minus the gauntlets. The right side of his face is pitch black, and his right eye has a slit pupil.

As an "Erebus":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/2/20/ErebusPortrait.png], he foregoes his black undershirt, revealing that the black discoloration on his face extends to parts of his chest and torso.

title: skirmisher_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[demonic_lancer|Demonic Lancer]]. Also known as the Highlander or Durandal.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/f/f2/SkirmisherPortrait.png] has his purple hair appear windswept, and he wears a short light gray jacket with a dark gray shirt and pants. He also comes equipped with gray pauldrons, gauntlets and greaves.

As a "Durandal":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/d/d9/DurandalPortrait.png], his appearance is still mostly the same, save for trading the jacket for a light gray cape and black fingerless gloves instead of gauntlets.

title: female_crusader_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[female_priest_(dungeon_and_fighter)|female Priest]]. Also known as the Evangelist or Seraphim.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/b/b2/Female_Crusader_Portrait.jpg] has much of her outfit recolored white and gold, with the addition of a small blue and white [[mitre]] on her head and a white top resembling a cape.

As a "Seraphim":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/6/69/Seraphim_Portrait.jpg], her black hair is now wavy, while her outfit is now predominantly white, gold, and blue, with the length of her robes going past her legs. Two pairs of gold angel wings are seen on her back.

h4. See also

* [[Male crusader (dungeon and fighter)|]]

title: male_priest_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/8/82/MalePriestPortrait.png] is a muscular man with brown short hair, sidelocks and beard. He's dressed in black and gold priest vestments, a white jacket and white pants, with a golden cross hanging around his neck.

He's voice actor is [[Kusunoki Taiten]] in Japanese version, [[Jo Gyuchun]] in Korean version and [[Liu Beichen]] in Chinese version.

Classes:
* [[male crusader (dungeon and fighter)|Crusader]] (Paladin, Saint)
* [[monk_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Monk]] (Templar, Justice)
* [[exorcist_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Exorcist]] (Hyperion, Draconid)
* [[avenger_(dungeon_and_fighter)|Avenger]] (Doom Guardian, Immortal)

title: male_crusader_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male priest (dungeon and fighter)|male Priest]]. Also known as the Paladin or Saint.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/6/6e/CrusaderPortrait.png] trades in his base class's outfit for red and white priest vestments with a white hooded cape. His hair has grown to shoulder length along with his beard.

As a "Saint":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/b/bc/Saint.png], his hair is cut short and his facial hair trimmed to a stubble, resembling his base class more. His clothes are now predominantly white, with plate armor appearing on his arms, left shoulder and legs. The golden hammer he wields is his signature weapon, the Jupiter Hammer.

As a "Neo Crusader":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/6/67/Neo-_Male_Crusader_Artwork.png], his appearance is a combination of his Crusader hairstyle and outfit and his Saint outfit's armor, along with a slight redesign of the Jupiter Hammer featuring more cross imagery.

h4. See also

* [[Female Crusader_(dungeon_and_fighter)|]]

title: agent_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/2/26/Gunblader_Portrait.png] is a bespectacled middle-aged man with dark skin and short gray hair. His outfit consists of a long white jacket, green dress shirt and vest, brown leather pistol holster and utility belt, black pants and brown boots.

Subclasses:

title: secret_agent_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[Agent (dungeon and fighter)|]]. Also known as the Enforcer or Executioner.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/7/71/Agent_Concept_Art.png] has his hair slicked back, wearing a green military vest with a white long-sleeved undershirt, various leather pistol and magazine holsters, black pants, black boots and black gloves.

As an "Executioner":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/a/a1/Requiem_Portrait.png], his undershirt is now black and he also wears a dark gray trenchcoat.

title: specialist_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[agent (dungeon and fighter)|Agent]]. Also known as the Core Master or Pathfinder.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/0/0b/Specialist_Full_Body_Art.png] features messy, swept back hair, held back by a pair of blue goggles on his head. He wears a shorter beige coat with several pockets and blue lights on its shoulders, with similar blue lights on his brown leather belt; he otherwise appears the same as his base class.

As a "Pathfinder":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/0/08/Pathfinder_Portrait.png], he loses the goggles and leaves his messy hair down. He now wears a longer white coat and much of the remainder of his outfit has been recolored blue.

title: hitman_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[agent (dungeon and fighter)|Agent]]. Also known as the Big Boss or Godfather.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/c/ca/Hitman_Full_Body_Art.png] has a look that's almost exactly the same as his base class, with the only notable difference being that his hair is parted to the left.

As a "Godfather":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/b/b0/Godfather_Portrait.png], his hair is parted in the opposite direction and he sports an olive green coat and black dress vest. In the background, two of his fellow Agents - one in a white coat and another in black - are seen firing at off-screen enemies.

title: troubleshooter_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[agent (dungeon and fighter)|Agent]]. Also known as the Wild Card or Renegade.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/1/18/Trouble_Shooter_Concept_Art.png] gives him shoulder-length hair and [[pince-nez]] sunglasses. He trades in his white coat for a beige poncho concealing a variety of grenades underneath.

As a "Renegade":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/5/5d/Untouchable_Portrait.png], his hair has been styled into a thin ponytail, his poncho has been recolored dark gray, and his glasses were removed. He also sports a long, white cape.

title: male_launcher_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male gunner (dungeon and fighter)|Gunner]]. Also known as the Wrecking Ball or Destroyer.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/3/3b/Male_LauncherPortrait.png] is similar to his base class, with the only differences being that his right sleeve is hanging off his shoulder and a leather shoulder pad present on his left shoulder. He wields a gatling gun, being one of his sub-weapon skills.

As a "Destroyer":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/5/58/Dnf_season_4_destroyer_by_toonegeminielf-d7nu8f5.png], he wears a black military outfit with a sleeveless top and magazine harness, dual wielding a pair of laser cannons.

His "Neo Launcher":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/2/24/Neo-_Male_Launcher_Artwork.png] appearance gives him a sleeved red top, and is now wielding a railgun. In the background is a satellite cannon, one of the new skills he gains as a Neo Launcher.

title: male_mechanic_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male gunner (dungeon and fighter)|Gunner]]. Also known as the Machinist or Prime.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/b/b9/MechanicPortrait.png] is similar to his base class, with the purple trenchcoat's top being undone and left hanging off of his waist. Accompanying him are several small robots, which he uses in combat.

As a "Prime":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/1/1f/Dnf_season_4_prime_by_toonegeminielf-d7nu8xr.png], he now has curled hair and no longer has his purple trenchcoat, instead wearing a red hooded vest. He's also seen wielding a submachine gun, his class's weapon of choice.

His "Neo Mechanic":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/9/92/Neo-_Male_Mechanic_Artwork.png] appearance is generally the same as his Prime outfit, now wearing glasses and a long red jacket. Green goggles hang around his neck.

title: male_ranger_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male gunner (dungeon and fighter)|Gunner]]. Also known as the Raven or Desperado.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/d/d6/MaleRangerPortrait.png] features mostly the same clothing as his base class with the addition of a black cowboy hat. He wields the white-handled revolvers seen in his base class's art, with an upper body harness holstering two more revolvers.

As a "Raven":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/3/36/Dnf_season_4_raven_by_toonegeminielf-d7nu67r.png], his clothing is now black with red trimmings, swapping his old trenchcoat for an unzipped black one. Feathers from his namesake trail behind him.

His appearance as a "Neo Ranger":[https://wiki.dfo.world/images/f/f8/Neo-_Male_Ranger_Artwork.png] is mostly similar to his Raven outfit, with his jacket now being zipped and parts of his clothing in tatters, presumably due to gunfire. His revolvers feature short-bladed bayonets on them, much like his [[female_ranger_(dungeon_and_fighter)|female counterpart]].

title: summoner_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[Female Mage_(dungeon_and_fighter)|]]. Also known as the Lunar Princess or Eclipse.

Her default appearance has her red hair cut short and swept to her left. She wears a black jacket with a simple one-piece red dress underneath and dark gray stockings with black stripes. Her myriad summons are shrouded in darkness behind her.

As an Eclipse, her short hair has [[antenna_hair|hair antennae]] added to the top of her head (some fan artists alternatively depict it as a sole [[ahoge]]). Her outfit consists of a red jacket with white sleeves, a short red top, black shorts, and white kneesocks.

As a Neo Summoner, she has a longer black jacket, red and black dress, and red thighhighs.

h4. Appearance

* !asset #24660710: Default
* !asset #24660711: Eclipse
* !post #5353628: Neo Summoner

title: elementalist_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[Female Mage_(dungeon_and_fighter)|]]. Also known as the Archmage or Overmind.

Her default appearance has her side tail rearranged as a ponytail, with more natural bangs held by a pair of hair clips. She wears robes with white sleeves, red torso and black bottom, with a white skirt and black thighhighs.

As an Overmind, her hair has been arranged into twintails. The colors on her top are reversed and she's now wearing white thighhighs. She also wears a black headband with gold decorations on it.

As a Neo Elementalist, her hair is almost the length of her body and has a slight orange tinge at its ends. She wears robes that are now predominantly white with gold trim and a red skirt.

h4. Appearance

* !asset #24660697: Default
* !asset #24660698: Overmind
* !asset #24660699: Neo Elementalist

title: enchantress_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[Female Mage_(dungeon_and_fighter)|]]. Also known as the Black Maiden or Hekate.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/2/23/EnchantressPortrait.png] has her hair styled into short, thick twintails, wearing a solely black, frilled gothic lolita outfit. Her familiar, a patchwork teddy bear named Madd, is seen in the background attacking with purple thorned vines.

As a "Hekate":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/8/83/Hecate_Awakening.jpg], her hair is now waist length and her black dress is long enough to reach the floor. Her black stockings are replaced with black kneesocks, and she also wears a headdress with a black rose and gold butterfly decorations, covering her right eye. In the background, Madd sits behind a pile of destroyed dolls.

As a "Neo Enchantress":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/8/8b/Neo-_Enchantress_Artwork.jpg], her hair is almost her whole body in length and styled into curls. Her black dress is adorned by gold bone decorations and her headdress is replaced with a black bonnet. In the background, Madd is seen in a suit and opera mask, looking over a pile of burning dolls and thorns.

title: creator_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. A subclass of the [[Female Mage_(dungeon_and_fighter)|]] that has space-warping powers.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/a/a3/CreatorPortrait1.png] is a messy blonde-haired, blue-eyed young girl with pointy ears. She wears circle frame glasses, a black jacket with yellow stripes, a yellow dress, black shorts and almost knee-high boots. She's often also seen with a small brown bag wrapped across her torso.

Her "second Awakening":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/7/7a/Creator_Awakening.jpg] is almost exactly the same in appearance, save for a few added yellow details to her jacket and wearing black sneakers with knee-high socks. The floating metal lion head behind her is her familiar, an avatar of Cabala, one of the Time Lords.

title: witch_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[Female Mage_(dungeon_and_fighter)|]]. Also known as the Trickster or Geniewiz.

Her "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/f/f4/WitchPortrait.PNG] features her wearing a red one-piece dress, a black cape, black witch hat, and black shoes with curled ends. Some of her minor familiars are sitting atop of her head and shoulders. A bandage adorns her nose.

As a "Trickster":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/e/ea/New_Geniewiz.png], her hair is styled into twintails and has taken on a slightly pink tinge. Her witch hat is replaced with a comically large one, the top of her one-piece is white, and she now has a bandage on her cheek. She also wears a red capelet, black thighhighs, and carries around a small red bag with random tools and candy in it. Some of her homunculi are seen flying around in the background.

As a "Neo Witch":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/5/5d/Neo-_Witch_Artwork.jpg], she wears a long black and red jacket and her witch hat is of immense proportions. She wears black kneesocks, exposing some of the myriad bandages along her legs.

title: weapon_master_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male slayer (dungeon and fighter)|male Slayer]]. Also known as the Grand Master or Omniblade.

As a "Weapon Master":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/8/81/WeaponMasterPortrait.png], he retains mostly the same look as a Slayer, with the exception of his red arm turning white.

His appearance as an "Omniblade":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/1/1d/SwordGodPortrait.png] swaps his outfit out for a more Eastern-influenced one, with his "Neo Weapon Master":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/d/de/Neo-_Blade_Master_Artwork.jpg] outfit retaining mostly the same look, but with an open jacket and rice hat.

title: asura_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male slayer (dungeon and fighter)|male Slayer]]. Also known as the Silent Eye or Indra.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/7/79/AsuraPortrait.png] is similar to the base male Slayer's, with the exception of a black cape and black blindfold.

As an "Indra":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/8/8d/IndraPortrait.png], he instead takes on a more god-like appearance, having blue skin and a large, spiked halo behind him.

His appearance as a "Neo Asura":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/b/be/Neo-_Asura_Artwork.jpg] further cements his characterization as a god-like being by adding elements of Hindu and Buddhist iconography.

title: ghost_slayer_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body: A [[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character and subclass of the [[male slayer (dungeon and fighter)|Slayer]].

title: soul_bender_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male slayer (dungeon and fighter)|male Slayer]]. Also known as the Soul Reaper or Dark Lord.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/7/71/SoulBenderPortrait.png] is mostly the same, save for a purple aura and yellow runes appearing on his demon arm. He retains this look as a "Dark Lord":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/1/1d/DarkLordPortrait.png], save for the addition of skull-themed armor pieces.

As a "Neo Soul Bender":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/9/94/Neo-_Soul_Bender_Artwork.jpg], he sports predominantly black clothing and a demon-themed visor replaces the Slayer's blue headband.

title: ghostblade_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. Subclass of the [[male slayer (dungeon and fighter)|male Slayer]]. Also known as the Yaksha or Rakshasa.

Unlike the other four Slayer subclasses, the "Ghostblade":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/3/3c/GhostBladePortrait.png] has a distinctly different appearance from his base class, having long hair, tattered clothing, and a blue demon arm instead of a red one. He is possessed by an unnamed ghostly familiar that aids him in combat, similar in build to the Ghostblade himself with almost the opposite coloration - black hair, coal-like skin, and a tattered maroon hakama.

As a "Rakshasa":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/c/c6/Rakshasa_Awakening.jpg], his hair is spikier and blue crystals have grown on his upper body and demon arm.

As a "Neo Ghostblade":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/1/19/Neo-_Ghostblade.jpg], the duo switches hair and clothing colors.

title: dark_knight_(dungeon_and_fighter)
body:
[[dungeon_and_fighter|Dungeon & Fighter]] character. A unique variation of the [[male slayer (dungeon and fighter)|Slayer]] that has time-warping powers.

His "default appearance":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/0/0e/DarkKnightPortrait1.png] has his white hair parted to the left, with yellow eyes whose sclerae have turned black. He wears a white vest, white pants and white greaves, all lightly decorated with gold diamond patterns. Unlike the Slayer, his demonic arm is black instead of red, with the chains binding it being gold instead of gray.

His "second Awakening":[https://wiki.dfo-world.com/images/0/06/Dark_Knight_Awakening_Fullbody.png] recolors much of his clothing black and gives his skin a slightly purple tinge.

title: buront
body:
Originally from [[2channel]]'s message boards, Buront is the name of a poster whose unusual phrases and brash attitude quickly made him a celebrity. 

A fan of the MMORPG [[Final Fantasy XI]] and the fighting game series [[Guilty Gear]], Buront generally appears in images as an [[Elvaan]] [[Paladin (final fantasy)|]] wielding a Gluttony Sword. His hatred of ninjas is legendary.

His signature attack is "Megaton Punch".

His unusual phrases are well known as "burontism" and someone who uses it is called a "burontist". As common net slang, by 2010, burontism and Buront himself appeared in some games, a cover page of a magazine, and the April Fool's event of an official page.

h4. External links

* "Burontism libraries":http://www.geocities.jp/burontosan/ 
* "Parallel translation of Burontism":http://wiki.livedoor.jp/buront/d/%a5%d6%a5%ed%a5%f3%a5%c8%b3%a4%a4%f2%c5%cf%a4%eb

title: katsudon_(food)
body:
A [[rice bowl]] topped with [[katsu_(food)|]], a deep-fried pork cutlet.

The most common recipe uses a flavoring sauce, onions and beaten eggs. However, there are other variations, including one well-known recipe which uses Worcestershire sauce and shredded cabbage. To differentiate the two, the former is sometimes called "[i]Tamago-toji [bound-together-with-egg] katsudon[/i]," whereas the latter is called "[i]Sauce Katsudon[/i]."

A common trope in Japanese crime dramas is for the detective to eat katsudon while interrogating a suspect. The typical heart-of-gold type detective would think, "if this guy goes to the slammer, he'd never be able to eat anything as good as this again," and then use his own coin to order a katsudon delivered straight to the suspect's house. Then the suspect would be moved so much as to turn himself in and confess to the crime, tears streaming down his face. And so goes the cliche. For these stories, there is an explanation that katsudon was the most expensive food that one could get on a police officer's salary. 

This is nowadays only seen as a joke or stereotype, but Japanese people have come up with the expression, "let someone eat katsudon," which carries the same meaning as "read someone their Miranda rights" (see post #1184509).

title: soobrazitelny_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]]'s personification of the Soviet destroyer [i]Soobrazitelny[/i], the second of five [i]Storozhevoy[/i]-class destroyers built for the Black Sea Fleet.

h4. History
Historically ordered as a sister ship of [[Grozny (Azur Lane)|]] and the other [i]Gnevny[/i]-class destroyers, she was reordered to the new [i]Storozhevoy[/i] design, itself the result of [[Hunter (Azur Lane)|]]'s battle damage in the Spanish Civil War reaching Joseph Stalin's war meeting and his request for all destroyers to use alternating boiler and engine rooms for survival.

Commissioned in 1941, she was primarily assigned to shore bombardment and convoy duties. Post-war, she was used as a rescue ship. A 1965 attempt by veterans to have her preserved as a museum ship on account of her battle record was unsuccessful and was sold for scrap afterward.

title: wattson_(apex_legends)
body:
Wattson is a playable Legend in [[Apex Legends]], added to the game in season 2.

Wattson has [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. Her most distinctive feature is a [[burn scar]] on her left cheek in the shape of a [[Lichtenberg figure]]. Her default costume consists of a [[hooded bodysuit|hooded]] [[blue bodysuit|blue]] [[ribbed bodysuit]] worn under a [[white bodysuit]] with [[cable]]s and an [[orange jacket|orange]] [[hooded jacket]] with a [[lightning bolt symbol]] on the upper arm. She also wears [[blue gloves]] and [[white footwear|white]] [[sneakers]].

She is often pictured wielding an [[L-STAR]], as the weapon was added to the game at the same time as her, and her heirloom weapon is the [[Energy Reader (apex legends)|]]. She has a pet [[cat]] named [[Nikola (apex legends)|]], and is notably fond of [[Nessie (respawn)|]] - to the point that she's credited as the person responsible for the plushies hidden around the various maps.

Wattson is voiced by "Justine Huxley":[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0404722/] in English and "Kondou Yui":[https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E8%BF%91%E8%97%A4%E5%94%AF#%E3%82%B2%E3%83%BC%E3%83%A0] in Japanese.

title: asuka_(senran_kagura)
body:
[[Senran Kagura]] main character. A second-year Shinobi student and leader at the Hanzou Academy.

Asuka has [[black hair]], usually tied into a medium length [[ponytail]] with a [[white ribbon]]. When she transforms into a shinobi, she wears a yellow [[vest]] over a [[white shirt]] and [[green necktie]]. With it she wears a [[green dress|green]] [[plaid dress]] and a [[red scarf]]. She wears red arm guards over [[bandages]], and [[thighhighs]] with [[brown footwear|brown]] [[shoes]]. She is usually seen with her twin [[sword]]s.

Asuka's favorite food is futomaki rolls. She fights for justice and wants to follow in the footsteps of her grandfather Hanzou, a legendary shinobi of his time. Sheer willpower and determination is what drives her to master the way of the shinobi. Firm believer that the Sword and Shield's true power comes from using both. Her guardian animal is the toad. 

When her clothes are ripped off, she is revealed to be wearing a simple [[striped bikini]].

Her seiyuu is [[Harada Hitomi]].

h4. External links

* "Kagurapedia: Asuka":https://senrankagura.fandom.com/wiki/Asuka

title: huohuo_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]].

A trainee Ten-Lords Commission Judge of the Xianzhou Luofu, she is a young [[fox girl|Foxian girl]] possessed by a [[Tail (Honkai: Star Rail)|heliobus]]. She is a timid and weak girl who is afraid of all kinds of strange things, but is responsible for luring and subduing evil spirits. Voiced by [[Naganawa Maria]].

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[green hair]] with an [[ahoge]], and [[green eyes]] with [[paw-shaped pupils]]. Her default outfit consists of a [[black hat|black]] [[dianzi]], [[green dress]] with [[detached sleeves]], [[brown belt]], [[loose socks|loose]] [[white socks]], and dark [[blue footwear|blue shoes]]. She also normally carries an improvised white [[flag]]. 

h4. Appearance

* !post #7691346: Splash art
* !post #8768426: Night of Fright (signature Light Cone)

h4. Profile
[expand]
A pitiable and helpless Foxian girl who is also a Ten-Lords Commission Judge-in-training, who fears ghosts but must catch them.

Due to having a heliobus named Tail sealed in her tail by the judges of the Ten-Lords Commission, she became a "cursed one" who attracts inhuman beings.

She fears demons and heliobi, but contrarily is tasked with their capture and entrusted with the heavy task of eradicating vile spirits.
Though she believes herself lacking in ability, she is unable to muster the courage to resign and continues onward despite walking in a valley of her own fear.

title: fu_xuan_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]].

She is the head of the Xianzhou Luofu's Divination Commission. She manages the Xianzhou Luofu's route by calculating it and predicts the fortune of future events. Voiced by [[Itou Miku]] in Japanese. 

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[pink hair]], [[yellow eyes]], [[small breasts]], and a [[forehead jewel]]. Her default outfit consists of a [[sleeveless]] [[layered dress]] ([[black dress|black]] outer and purple-[[pink dress|pink]] inner), [[white pantyhose]], [[vambraces]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[pumps]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #7690465: Splash art
* !post #8768517: She Already Shut Her Eyes (Signature Light Cone)

h4. Profile
[expand]
The head of the Xianzhou Luofu's Divination Commission. A confident and blunt sage.

Using her third eye and the Matrix of Prescience, Fu Xuan calculates the Xianzhou's route and predicts the fortune of future events. She firmly believes that everything she does is the "best solution" for the situation.

Fu Xuan is waiting for the general's promised "abdication." However, that day still seems... very far away.
[/expand]

title: seele_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]]. Voiced by [[Nakahara Mai]] (JP) and [[Molly Zhang]] (EN).  

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[purple hair]] with an [[ahoge]], [[purple eyes]] that turn [[red eyes|red]] upon using her ultimate, and [[medium breasts]]. Her default outfit consists of a purple [[detached collar]], [[black bra]] top, [[white leotard]], purple [[detached sleeves]] with a [[red armband]] to her left side, [[black shorts|black]] [[short shorts]], [[single glove|single]] [[black gloves|black glove]] on her right hand, and [[black footwear|black]] [[boots]]. She uses a [[scythe]] as her main weapon. 

h4. Appearance

* !post #7689970: Splash art
* !post #8768327: In the Night (signature Light Cone)

h4. Profile
[expand]
A spirited and valiant member of Wildfire who grew up in the perilous Underworld of Belobog. She is accustomed to being on her own.

As someone who once relied on others for protection, she now pursues strength. For the truth of the underground and her family's name, Seele can endure any kind of adversity.

The protectors and the protected, the oppressors and the oppressed... The world Seele grew up knowing was just a simple dichotomy...

That is, until "that girl" appeared.
[/expand]

h4. See also

* [[Seele Vollerei]] - her [[Honkai Impact 3rd]]/[[Benghuai Xueyuan]] counterpart.
** Specifically, she combines the color scheme of HI3 Seele's [[Seele Vollerei (Swallowtail Phantasm)|Swallowtail Phantasm]] form with the red eyes of [[Seele (Alter Ego)|the Alter Ego]] form.

title: bailu_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]]. Voiced by [[Katou Emiri]] in Japanese. 

She is portrayed with [[very long hair|very long]] [[purple hair]] with [[antenna hair|two ahoge]] and tied into [[twin braids]], [[green eyes]], [[pointy ears]], and [[dragon horns]] and [[dragon tail|tail]]. Her default outfit consists of a [[black dress]] worn under a [[white coat|white]] [[wave print]] [[duijin ruqun]] with [[detached sleeves]] and [[fur trim]], a [[gourd]] to her left, [[blue socks]], and [[black footwear|black shoes]]. 

Her race is the [[dragon girl|Vidyadhara]], and serves as its current High Elder. 

h4. Appearance
* !post #7691280: Splash art
* !post #8768102: Time Waits for No One (signature Light Cone)

h4. Profile
[expand]
A vivacious young lady of the Vidyadhara race, she is known as the "Healer Lady" due to her expertise with medicine.

She often dishes out unorthodox prescriptions such as "Stay well hydrated" and "Get a good night's rest."

Bailu cannot bear to see people suffer, and that's why you'll see her with her eyes shut tightly as she cures ailments.

"As long as they're cured, that's all that matters, right?"
[/expand]

h4. See also
* [[Baiheng (honkai: star rail)|]]

title: wing_gundam_zero_custom
body:
The XXXG-00W0 Wing Gundam Zero Custom is the mobile suit featured in the [[gundam wing: endless waltz|film version]] of [[gundam_wing|Mobile Suit Gundam Wing]].

It is a highly redesigned unit by [[Katoki Hajime]], and can easily be distinguished from the original [[Wing Gundam Zero]] (designed by [[Ookawara Kunio]]) or the Proto Zero (also designed by Katoki) by having 4 large, angel-like [[wings]], a redesigned Twin [[Buster Rifle]] (which is now also longer in this version), and the absence of a shield and transformation system (although [i]The Glory of Losers[/i] manga, the Hi-Res Model, and the Master Grade Ver.Ka [[GunPla]] kit brought back the shield and transformation system).

title: after_war_gundam_x
body:
[b]After War Gundam X[/b] is the third [[alternate universe]] series in the [[Gundam]] franchise. It features an alternate outcome to the One Year War in the original series (Universal Century 0079) and ran for 39 episodes.

For the mobile suit, see [[gundam_x|Gundam X]].

title: gundam_x
body:
[b]GX-9900 Gundam X[/b]

A powerful [[Mobile Suit]] developed by the Earth Alliance to fight the Spacenoids' looming threat of colony drops. Equipped with the massively powerful [[Satellite Cannon]], it could wipe out a colony with one shot. While most of them were destroyed in the war, one surviving unit made its way into the hands of everyman [[Garrod Ran]], who wielded its terrifying power to protect his "mission target" - the cute but enigmatic [[Tiffa Adill]].

title: shining_finger
body:
[i]This hand of mine glows with an awesome power. 
Its burning grip tells me to defeat you!
Take this! My love, my anger, and all of my sorrow!
[b]SHINING FINGER! GO! GO! GO![/b][/i]

--[[Domon Kasshu]], [i][[G Gundam|Mobile Fighter G Gundam]][/i]

A special move used by [[Domon Kasshu]]'s [[Shining Gundam]] in [[G Gundam]]. It envelops the right or left hand with glowing, hot energy and is then used to crush an enemy Gundam's head. 

There are two other variants of the move: [[Master Gundam]]'s ([[Master Asia]]) Darkness Finger and [[God Gundam]]'s (Domon Kasshu) [[Bakunetsu God Finger]]. [[Turn X]] ([[Gym Ghingnham]], [i][[Turn A Gundam]][/i]) also uses a version of the Shining Finger.

[[Destiny Gundam]]'s ([[Shinn Asuka]], [i][[Gundam SEED Destiny]][/i]) Palma Fiocina and [[Guren Mk-ii]]'s ([[Kouzuki Kallen]], [i][[Code Geass]][/i]) Fukushahadou are similar, but not exactly the same as the Shining Finger. Do not use this tag with these two [[mecha]] unless it's a direct imitation or parody.

Use this tag for all variants of the move being used, and (for [[parody]] purposes) if the character's hand appears to be "glowing with an awesome power" or "burning red".
other_names: シャイニングフィンガー

title: bakunetsu_god_finger
body:
The [[God Gundam]]'s finishing move, essentially a more powerful version of the [[Shining Finger]]. 

Like the Shining Finger, the Bakunetsu God Finger also envelopes the right or left hand with glowing, hot energy. One difference is that while the former targets an opponent Gundam's head, the latter targets the midsection instead, which is then followed by the [i]Heat End[/i] maneuver, where the God Gundam discharges all of its energy at once while its hand is still plunged into an opponent's body, destroying it from the inside out.

It is renamed to [b]Erupting Burning Finger[/b] in the English dub.
other_names: 爆熱ゴッドフィンガー

body:

title: doctor_fate
body: Doctor Fate (also known as Fate) is the name of several superheroes appearing in American comic books published by [[DC Comics]]. Eight characters have served as incarnations of the character within the mainstream DC Universe, with each new version after the original attempting to reinvigorate the character for contemporary audiences.

title: mike_(fate)
body: A minor character appearing in the [[Avalon le Fae (fate/grand order)|]] chapter of [[Fate/Grand Order]]. An Earth Clan fairy who runs an inn and pub, but doesn't really understand how they are supposed to work because he has never interacted with humans. He becomes infatuated with [[leonardo_da_vinci_(rider)_(fate)| Da Vinci]] as she teaches him how to run an inn properly. [spoiler]At the conclusion of the chapter, the Mors corruption begins to drive Mike insane and almost causes him to murder Da Vinci, but in the end his feelings win out and he sees her off with a smile as the Lostbelt fades away.[/spoiler]

body:

title: shimakaze_(kancolle)
body:
[b]Shimakaze[/b] (島風, lit. "Island Wind") is the personification of the Japanese destroyer [i]Shimakaze[/i] in [[Kantai Collection]]. 

Shimakaze has [[long_hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] and [[grey eyes]]. She wears a [[crop top|cropped]] [[serafuku]], [[striped thighhighs]], [[white_gloves|white]] [[elbow gloves]], a short [[miniskirt]] with [[black_panties|black]] [[highleg panties]] which show off her [[ass]], and a [[black hairband]] with long floppy "ears". She has small robot familiars called [[Rensouhou-chan]]s which represent her three twin "12.7 cm/50 naval gun":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/12.7_cm/50_Type_3_naval_gun turrets.

h4. Personality and trivia
As she is based on an experimental destroyer built around speed and heavy torpedo armaments, Shimakaze sports a boastful personality, occasionally bragging about how fast she is and nitpick on how "slow" those around her are. In spite of this, due to the historical counterpart only experienced few combat actions (being mostly used as an escort), Shimakaze also have a lazy, "spoiled brat" altitude, being generally carefree and minding her own business rather than the others.

While the historical ship is the fastest bluewater ship in the IJN fleet, she is not the fastest destroyer in the game after the inclusion of [[Tashkent (kancolle)|]] around 2018. After this, Shimakaze is often depicted in fan works as either losing her confidence or viewed Tashkent as a rival she swears to surpass.

Due to her distinctive and revealing outfit, she has become one of the most popular characters of the series, with several artists often drawing the other characters [[cosplay]] [[shimakaze (kancolle) (cosplay)|as her]]. She is also frequently portrayed as an [[otoko no ko]] ([[Shimakaze-kun]]) or as an unrelated boy [[crossdressing]] as her.

Her fan nickname is [i]Zekamashi[/i], Shimakaze spelled backwards due to pre-1946 Japanese orthography reading horizontal writing right-to-left, after it was written on an [[innertube]] on a Rensouhou-chan.

Character design by [[Shizuma Yoshinori]], voiced by [[Sakura Ayane]].

title: shimakaze-kun
body:
An unofficial male version of [[Shimakaze (kancolle)|]] of [[Kantai Collection]].

Due to the revealing nature of the original's clothes, Shimakaze-kun will often be an identical-looking [[otoko no ko]].

Depending on context, Shimakaze-kun can be tagged two different ways:
* Usually, Shimakaze-kun is a male [[cosplay|cosplaying]] as Shimakaze. The context is the "real world", where Shimakaze is a memetic character from an online game and media franchise.  This should be tagged [[shimakaze (kancolle) (cosplay)]].
* Less commonly, he may be the actual Shimakaze but male. It may be an alternate reality where Shimakaze was always male, or Shimakaze may have been transformed into a male by some event. The context is the world of Kantai Collection, where Shimakaze is a real person. This should be tagged [[genderswap (ftm)]].

Where insufficient context exists, tagging is up to user discretion, but be consistent. In particular, the first case implies the character is "not really" Shimakaze, while the second implies the character "really" is. Thus they are generally mutually exclusive.

title: prince_hongzhou
body:
[b]Hongzhou[/b] (Chinese:弘昼, Manchurian Script: ᡥᡠᠩᠵᡝᠣ) (5 January 1712 – 2 September 1770), formally known as Prince He, was a Manchu prince of the [[Qing dynasty]]. 

Unlike his brothers Hongli and Hongshi, Hongzhou chose to avoid being involved in rivalry over the succession to their father's throne. He was known to have pretended to be crazy and feminine.

title: bolzano_(azur_lane)
body:
[i][[Azur Lane]][/i]'s personification of the Italian heavy cruiser [i]Bolzano[/i]. Character design by [[Haori Io]], voiced by Maekawa Ryouko. 

She is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]] tied to a [[single braid]], [[red eyes]], and [[large breasts]]. 

Her default outfit consists of a [[black dress]] with a white breast side, armor pieces on her waists, [[white hat|white]] [[peaked cap]], [[white skirt|white]] [[pleated skirt]], [[two-sided fabric|two-tone]] coat ([[white coat|white]] outer with [[epaulettes]], [[green coat|green]] inner), [[mismatched legwear|mismatched thighhighs]] ([[white thighhighs|white]] on her left, [[black thighhighs|black]] on her right), black [[thigh strap]] on her right leg, [[black gloves|black]] [[elbow gloves]] (with a single [[gauntlets|gauntlet]] on her right), and [[grey footwear|grey]] [[high heels]]. 

Her [[rigging]] consists of two separate hull pieces, each containing two 20.3 cm twin gun mounts, a 10 cm twin [[anti-aircraft gun]] mount, a mast, and a gunnery director.

title: jiangyu_(neural_cloud)
body:
An Agent in [[Girls' Frontline Neural Cloud]]. A Performer Doll developed by Cyber Media, a past instance of [[Type 97 (girls' frontline)|]] and sister of [[Daiyan (Neural Cloud)|]].

Jiangyu has very [[very long hair|very long]] [[black hair]] in [[twintails]] and [[red eyes]]. Her normal costume consists of a [[white shirt|white]] [[crop top]] with a [[detached collar]], a [[red necktie]] and [[black straps]] framing a [[see-through shirt]], black [[detached sleeves]], [[black shorts|black]] [[short shorts]], [[white thighhighs|white]] [[thighhighs]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[boots]], as well as [[black gloves|black]] [[fingerless gloves]]. When compared to Type 97 in the original [[Girls' Frontline]], she has almost the same appearance save for the skirt being shorts and her [[midriff]] being visible.

As a result of Jiangyu's Live2D artist posting a non-official "animation":[/posts/5995283] of her doing a [[fellatio gesture]], paired with her outfit, she's often rendered in a lewd fashion in fanart.

h4. Appearance

title: wa2000_(girls'_frontline)
body:
An android representing the [[Walther WA 2000]] in [[Girls' Frontline]]. 

She has [[long hair|long]] [[purple hair]] done in a [[half updo]], [[red eyes]], [[large breasts]], and wears a black [[blazer]], [[red necktie]], [[black skirt]], [[black pantyhose]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]].

A total [[tsundere]] towards everyone. Based off her in-game lines this is due to her viewing herself solely as a weapon and finding it hard to effectively communicate with others as a result. The tone of her lines can also depend based on language, with the JP voice lines being a lot harsher on the tsuntsun than the CN text lines. She's also infamous for being a terrible cook.

She is voiced by [[Tomatsu Haruka]]. In the sequel [[Girls' Frontline 2: Exilium]], WA2000 appears as [[Makiatto (girls' frontline 2)|]].

title: rpk-16_(girls'_frontline)
body:
An android representing the [[RPK-16]] [[machine gun]] in [[Girls' Frontline]]. One of the members of team [[DEFY (girls' frontline)|]].

She has [[short hair|short]] [[grey hair]], [[purple eyes]] and wears a [[tactical clothes]], [[black bodysuit]], and [[black shorts]].

She gives the impression of being a cheerful, chatty girl who's very easy-going and comfortable to be around. But when you gradually drop your guard, she will often say bewildering things that astonish you... You will see a whole different side of this Doll as you spend more time with her.

Voiced by [[Fuchigami Mai]] and illustrated by [[Duoyuanjun]].

title: isomer_hivemind_(girls'_frontline)
body:
A Nyto type that first appeared in the Shattered Connexion event. The leader of the abandoned [[Isomer (girls' frontline)|]]s, acting as the representative of the Isomer Hivemind that had developed in Tallinn. Called "Failed Isomer" in the in-game Enemy Units Index, with her two forms referred to as "Isomer White" and "Isomer Black" in the community.

Originally [spoiler]an Isomer who took over the body of the discarded [[Nimogen (girls' Frontline)|Nimogen]].[/spoiler] By the end of SC, [spoiler]she and the other Isomers were assimilated by M4A1's OGAS, who then subsequently took over the body and was later dubbed [[Dandelion (girls' frontline)|]].[/spoiler]

title: kamen_rider_zero-one
body:
Titular protagonist of [[kamen rider 01 (series)|Kamen Rider Zero-One]], thirtieth show of the Kamen Rider series and very first of the Reiwa generation, with the accession of Emperor Naruhito at the start of May 2019.

Hiden Aruto is a high-school student and aspiring stage comedian who reluctantly takes up his recently-deceased grandfather's position as president of Hiden Intelligence, Japan's leading specialist in HumaGears, humanoid robots with advanced artificial intelligence, in order to be able to access the president-exclusive powers of Kamen Rider Zero-One and protect humanity from rogue HumaGears hijacked by a cyberterrorist organization, with the aid of a specialized military unit and their own Riders.

As Zero-One, Aruto uses keycard-like Progrise Keys to transform into different animal-themed forms, including his default grasshopper-themed Rising Hopper.

title: 30_rock
body:
30 Rock is an American satirical sitcom created by Tina Fey that aired from October 11, 2006, to January 31, 2013 for seven seasons on NBC.

Based on Tina Fey's experience as a head writer on [[Saturday Night Live]], the series follows Liz Lemon(played by Tina Fey) as head writer and showrunner of the fictional sketch comedy show, TGS with Tracy, located at 30 Rockefeller Plaza, New York(30 Rock), where SNL is produced in [[Real Life]]. 

The show is famous not only for it's surreal humor but also of making fun of the tv network the show airs on, NBC, and the corporate owners of the network, General Electric and Comcast.

title: imminent_uno_loss_(meme)
body:
A [[meme]] based on an image of a woman playing an [[Uno (game)|]] card game, smiling confidently as she has only one card left in her hand. However, her opponent's hand is full of Draw 4 (and sometimes Draw 2) cards that can easily defeat her.

Sometimes, the hand is substituted with [b]all five pieces of [[Exodia the Forbidden One]][/b], which results in an instant win when revealed in [[Yu-Gi-Oh!]]

Spiked in popularity with the release of [[mimukauwa_nice_try_(vocaloid)|Mimukauwa Nice Try]], a song that features Miku undergoing this exact fate.

A 1994 Super Famicom role-playing game developed by Square. The game was initially a failure compared to Final Fantasy, selling only 270,000 copies. title: oersted
body:
One of the main characters in [[Live A Live]] and main protagonist of The Middle Ages: The Lord of Dark chapter. A knight of the Kingdom of Lucrece who embarked on a journey to rescue Princess [[Alethea]], who was abducted by the Lord of Dark.

[spoilers]At the end of the Middle Ages chapter, Oersted renounces his former ties and titles from Lucrece and took on the name "Odio", accepting his unwanted role as a demon and becoming the Lord of Dark after losing the faith of the people of Lucrece and having no one left to believe in him.[/spoilers]

[spoilers]He, as [[Demon King Odio|Odio, the Lord of Dark]], is playable in the Final Chapter if he is chosen as the protagonist. He is also playable for one turn at the very end of the 2022 remake's true final boss, dealing the final blow to the Sin of Odio.[/spoilers]

He is voiced by [[Nakamura Yuuichi]] in the 2022 remake.

title: streibough
body:
Character in [[Live A Live]]'s Middle Ages chapter. Wizard of Lucrece and [[Oersted]]'s closest companion for most of his journey to rescue Princess [[Alethea]] from the clutches of the Lord of Dark.

[spoilers]It is revealed that Streibough is the hidden main antagonist of the Middle Ages chapter, being responsible for the regicide of the King of Lucrece by Oersted's hand by masking the King's appearance as the Lord of Dark and Oersted's descent into becoming [[Demon King Odio|Odio]].[/spoilers]

[spoilers]His soul can be found in the Trial of Heart in the Dominion of Hate, questioning if he is to blame for Oersted's descent into becoming the Lord of Dark.[/spoilers]

He is voiced by Hodoshima Shizuma in the 2022 remake.

title: alethea
body:
Character in [[Live A Live]]'s Middle Ages chapter. The princess of the Kingdom of Lucrece who was abducted by the Lord of Dark pretty early in the chapter, prompting [[Oersted]] to embark on a journey to save her.

[spoilers]At the end of the Middle Ages chapter, she dumped Oersted for [[Streibough]], telling the former he came to save her too late. She kills herself in front of Oersted, her corpse laying on top of Streibough's. This is one of the reasons for Oersted's descent into becoming the Lord of Dark, [[Demon King Odio|Odio]].[/spoilers]

[spoilers]Her soul appears in the Trial of Heart in the Dominion of Hate after obtaining the Guts and Glory Glove, begging for the protagonists to stop Oersted, telling them that he doesn't know what he has become.[/spoilers]

She is voiced by [[Arakawa Miho]] in the 2022 remake.

title: mavka
body:
Mavka (Ukrainian: Мавка) also Nyavka (Ukrainian: Нявка) is a type of female spirit in Ukrainian folklore and mythology. The Mavka is a long-haired figure, a Soul of the Forest, typically depicted as temptress figures who lure men to their deaths.

The spirits known by this term represented the souls of girls who had died unnatural, tragic or premature deaths, particularly unchristened babies. Mavkas often appear in the form of beautiful young girls who entice and lure young men into the woods, where they "tickle" them to death. Mavkas have no reflection in water, nor do they cast shadows. In some accounts, they were also said to help farmers by looking after cattle and driving out wild animals.

title: uranohoshi_school_uniform
body:
The [[school uniform]] worn by students who attend the Uranohoshi Girls' High School in [[Love Live! Sunshine!!]], it's a [[serafuku]] and comes in 3 versions.

The main [[summer uniform]] consists of a [[white shirt|white]], [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[grey sailor collar|sailor]] blouse and a [[grey skirt|grey]] [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[miniskirt]], and a [[neckerchief]] with a [[tie clip]]. The neckerchief may also be colored according to class year: students who first enter high school in Season 1 wear [[yellow neckerchief|yellow]], those in their second year wear [[red neckerchief|red]], and those in their third year wear [[aqua neckerchief|aqua]].

The [[winter uniform]] replaces the light blouse with a thicker [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]], [[double-breasted]] one and the neckerchief with a [[bowtie]] matching their neckerchief (although [[Matsuura Kanan|the]] [[kurosawa dia|third]] [[ohara mari|years]] opt to keep the neckerchief instead).

There is also an alternate [[black serafuku]] version of the winter uniform with a [[white neckerchief]] and [[tie clip]], featured in [[love live! sunshine!! the school idol movie over the rainbow|the movie]].

title: kamen_rider_drive
body:
Lead Rider of [[kamen_rider_drive_(series)|Kamen Rider Drive]], twenty-fifth show in the Kamen Rider series and sixteenth of the Heisei generation.

[[Tomari Shinnosuke]] was an ace police detective demoted to a special investigations division due to dismotivation following an incident where one of his colleagues was crippled. When his new team was assigned to look after cases of people suddenly becoming immobile, however, Shinnosuke was given a chance to reignite his passion with the super-car Tridoron and its sentient belt to transform into Kamen Rider Drive and fight the Roidmudes, monsters connected to the freezing incidents.

In a departure from series tradition, Drive is the first Rider to primarily use a car for transportation, and uses Shift Cars to either change his appearance and/or arsenal.

title: forbidden_gundam
body:
[b]GAT-X252 Forbidden Gundam[/b]

A second generation GAT-X mobile suit, the Forbidden gundam was a monstrous assault mobile suit, dedicated to devastating high-speed assaults against enemy fortifications and bases. It bore several unique weapons and systems including: two arm mounted 115mm machine guns, two 88mm backpack mounted railguns, a devastatingly powerful "Plasma Induction Cannon" capable of total annihilation of targets, worst yet the beam could  [b][i]bend[/i][/b] in order to hit moving targets. And finally a heavy scythe for close combat. The entire MS was protected by the now near standard trans-phase shift armor and a powerful electromagnetic field generator known as Geschmeidig Panzer. This unit was deployed by the Terrorist organization [[Blue Cosmos]] and was finally destroyed in combat by [[Yzak Joule]] and his [[Duel Gundam]].

title: whispy_woods
body:
A recurring boss in the [[Kirby (series)|]] series, Whispy Woods is usually the first boss enemy [[Kirby]] has to face in his adventures. He is known for being one of the easiest bosses for Kirby to fight - He's a (usually) stationary tree that drops apples on Kirby to attack, so all Kirby has to do is inhale the apples that drop and spit them back at him while standing next to him to avoid the air bullets he spits out. Whispy has appeared in many games ever since the very first one and sometimes takes a spot other than Level 1 in a game, and sometimes even changes strategy and gains new attacks, but that doesn't make him any tougher. A similar boss named King Golem who appears in Kirby & The Amazing Mirror also shares the same attack pattern as Whispy.

In the [[kirby:_right_back_at_ya|anime]], Whispy takes a different role. Instead of being a major enemy, Whispy serves as an ally to Kirby and his friends. He is very kind to his friends, yet shows no mercy to those who threaten his kingdom and forest. At first, he thought Kirby and his friends were intruders and tried to crush them as punishment. But after realizing [[King Dedede]] used him, Whispy becomes Kirby's friend while Dedede tries many times to cut down his forest (yet fails every time). In the [[Super Smash Bros.]] games, Whispy appears in the background, often minding his own business before taking deep breaths and then blowing strong winds that push players close to the edges of the Kirby stages he is placed in.

For more info, see his "wiki page":https://wikirby.com/wiki/Whispy_Woods.

title: dottore_(genshin_impact)
body:
Il Dottore, also known by his codename "The Doctor", is the second of the Eleven Fatui Harbingers and a major antagonist in [[Genshin Impact]]. He first appeared in the supplementary manga before his first in-game appearance.

Prior to becoming a Fatui Harbinger, he was a researcher from Sumeru known as [b]Zandik[/b]. He was exiled from his homeland for performing unethical experiments and "enhancing" humans. [[Pierro (genshin impact)|]] would later recruit him to join the Fatui. He finds his name "humorously ironic."

Like the other Fatui Harbingers, he is named after a stock character in the Italian theater genre "Commedia dell'arte":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Commedia_dell%27arte].

title: ayakashi_triangle
body:
Ayakashi Triangle, sometimes abbreviated as AyaTri, is a 2020-to-2023 Japanese manga series written and illustrated by [[Yabuki Kentarou]]. It has been serialized by publisher Shueisha since June 2020, changing from [[shounen jump|Weekly Shōnen Jump]] magazine to Shōnen Jump+ in April 2022.

The series focuses on exorcist ninja [[Kazamaki Matsuri]], as he tries to defend his childhood friend, the Ayakashi Medium [[Kanade Suzu]], from evil spirits called ayakashi. However, during a battle to save Suzu's life, Matsuri is turned into a girl after being cursed by [[Shirogane (ayatora)|]], the King of Ayakashi. With Suzu's help, Matsuri must adjust to his new feminine form as they deal with both the friendly and the malicious ayakashi they encounter, as well as their growing feelings for each other, all while trying to break Matsuri's curse for him to return to his original form.

h4.Characters

title: sun_quan
body:
[b]Sun Quan[/b] (孫權), courtesy name [b]Zhongmou[/b] (仲謀), posthumously known as Emperor Da of Wu (吳大帝), was the founder of the [[Eastern Wu|Eastern Wu dynasty]], one of the [[Romance of the Three Kingdoms|Three Kingdoms of China]]. 

After [[Sun Jian|Sun Jian's]] death in the early 190s, he and his family lived at various cities on the lower Yangtze River, until Sun Ce carved out a warlord regime in the Jiangdong region, based on his own followers and a number of local clan allegiances. When [[Sun Ce]] was assassinated, Sun Quan inherited the lands southeast of the Yangtze River from his brother. 

In winter of 207, the northern warlord [[Cao Cao]] led an army of approximately 220,000 to conquer the south to complete the reunification of China. Two distinct factions emerged at his court on how to handle the situation. One, led by [[Zhang Zhao]], urged surrender whilst the other, led by [[Zhou Yu]] and [[Lu Su]] and with support from a diplomatic mission by [[Zhuge Liang]], opposed Cao Cao. Eventually Sun Quan decided to ally with Liu Bei and employing the combined strategies of Zhou Yu and [[Huang Gai]], they defeated Cao Cao decisively at the Battle of Red Cliffs.

In late 220, [[Cao Pi]], King of Wei, Cao Cao's son and successor, seized the throne and proclaimed himself to be the Emperor of China, ending and succeeding the nominal rule of the Han dynasty. At first Sun Quan nominally served as a Wei vassal with the Wei-created title of King of Wu, but after Cao Pi demanded that he send his son [[Sun Deng]] as a hostage to the Wei capital Luoyang and he refused and declared himself independent by changing his era name. It was not until May 229 that he formally declared himself emperor.

After the death of his original crown prince, Sun Deng, two opposing factions supporting different potential successors slowly emerged. Sun Quan harshly settled the conflict between the two factions by exiling [[Sun He]] and forcing [[Sun Ba]] to commit suicide. Sun Quan died in May 252 at the age of 70 (by East Asian reckoning). He enjoyed the longest reign among all the founders of the Three Kingdoms and was succeeded by his son, [[Sun Liang]].

title: jaune_arc
body:
Jaune Arc is a male character from [[RWBY]], a 3DCG Series created by [[roosterteeth|Rooster Teeth]]. 

Jaune is the "J" in team JNPR and the leader of the team. His design and name are inspired by [[jeanne_d'arc|Joan of Arc]].

h4.Abilities

He wields a [[shield]] and [[sword]] collectively named [[crocea_mors_(rwby)| Crocea Mors]], which when combined together can become a even larger and wider sword. [spoiler]His semblance is Aura Amplifier, which lets him amplify his or someone else's aura; this can help people heal faster and use their semblances for longer.[/spoiler]

h4.Physical characteristics

Jaune is a 6'1" male who has short [[blonde_hair | blonde hair]] with [[blue_eyes | blue eyes]].

h4. Attire 

He wears a white [[breastplate]] with a gold outline and a [[black_hoodie | black hoodie]] underneath it. He also has [[armor]] on the side of both of his shoulders and below his elbow, continuing until it gets to his hand where it turns gold. he wears blue jeans that are tucked in to his [[brown_footwear | brown boots]].

title: feixiao_(honkai:_star_rail)
body:
A playable character in [[Honkai: Star Rail]]. Accompanied by [[Ecliptic Inner Beast (honkai: Star Rail)|]] in her Echo of War (weekly boss) version.

One of the seven generals of the Xianzhou Alliance and the commander of the Verdant Knights of the Yaoqing. Voiced by [[Komatsu Mikako]] in Japanese.

She is a [[fox girl]] with [[long hair|long]] [[grey hair]] with a [[blue hair|blue]] [[gradient hair|gradient end]], [[blue eyes]], [[eyeshadow]], and [[large breasts]]. Her default outfit consists of a [[sleeveless]] [[blue shirt]] worn alongside a [[wave print]] [[grey jacket]], [[white belt]], [[black shorts]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[knee boots]]. Unlike other Foxians, she does not have a [[fox tail]].

h4. Profile

"'The Merlin's Claw' is what's written in the books, and 'The Great General' is what people call me. The former sounds too formal, the latter too exaggerated. Neither suits me. I prefer my own title, the 'Lacking General' — lacking in worries, regrets, and rivals."

The Xianzhou Yaoqing's Merlin's Claw and one of the Seven Arbiter-Generals. Her personality is unrestrained and frank, dashing and straightforward. She is skilled in all forms of martial arts and has honed herself into a supreme weapon. She is widely adored by Xianzhou soldiers and civilians alike as "The Great General."

However, she bears the burden of the Moon Rage affliction. If she were to hunt down all the abominations in her limited lifetime — Then the only enemy Feixiao has would be herself.

title: mii_(nintendo)
body:
User avatars for [[Nintendo]]'s [[Wii]], [[nintendo 3ds|3DS]], and [[Wii U]] video game systems, appearing too on the [[Nintendo Switch]] in a lesser capacity. Typically [[chibi]] characters, sometimes without legs or arms (though inclusive of hands).

The Wii and the Wii U each have a unique set of Miis that appear as CPUs in Nintendo's games, the most well-known of the Wii set being [[Matt (wii)|]] (マット). However, Nintendo does make unique original Miis when needed; for instance, [[Nikki (swapnote)|]] for [[Swapnote]] and [[Sheila Bell]] for [[Surechigai Meikyuu]].

Numerous Nintendo games, such as [[Mario Kart]] (since Mario Kart Wii) and [[Super Smash Bros.]] allow players to use their Miis as playable characters. In the [[Super Smash Bros.]] series, the generic Miis used to represent the [[Mii Brawler|Brawler]], [[Mii Gunner|Gunner]], and [[Mii Swordfighter|Swordfighter]] types are shown to be based off the default Miis Guest C, Guest F, and Guest B.

Spiritually succeeded by the [[Sportsmate (nintendo)|]]s of [[Nintendo Switch Sports]], even if you can still play with and against Miis in that game.

h4. See also

* [[Mii Brawler]]
* [[Mii Gunner]]
* [[Mii Swordfighter]]

title: christian_louboutin_(brand)
body:
High-end [[fashion]] [[high heels]], characterized by their distinctive [[colored shoe soles|red-lacquered soles]] (not insoles). Blue soles were available for a limited time.

Note that not all of the heel is red; the side facing out will color-match the rest of the shoe.

title: greyscale_with_colored_background
body:
An image where the subject is in [[greyscale]] but the background is colored. It's usually also a [[simple background]].

Do not tag these as [[greyscale]], [[partially colored]] or [[spot color]].

If parts of the image other than the background are colored, such as the subject's eyes, [[spot color]] can be used. If the subject has enough coloring on itself that you'd tag it [[partially colored]], simply use that tag instead and do not tag it as greyscale with colored background.

h4. Examples

* !post #5782342
* !post #5576860

h4. See also

* [[monochrome background]]

title: partially_colored
body:
Some parts of a picture are colored, while others remain uncolored, left as a sketch or lineart. This is either because the image is [[unfinished]], or as way to draw attention to a subject.

For images that employ emphasis by use of limited colors, see [[spot color]] instead.

For posts where the only colored part is the background, use [[greyscale with colored background]] instead.

h4. Examples

* !post #5797637
* !post #7757806
* !post #5782023

h4. See also

* [[flat color]]
* [[Tag group:Colors]]

title: amaya_tsubame
body:
A character from [[Gakuen Idolmaster]], voiced by Yukari Amane (天音ゆかり Amane Yukari).

The vice president of Hatsuboshi Academy's student council and its current No.2 idol. Prideful of her abilities, she takes on a more pompous attitude. Though she's strict with herself and others, she's good at looking after them. She's a childhood friend and rival with [[juo_sena|Sena]], and has stated that she would surpass her and become "Prima Stella" in the future.

She has a [[long hair|long]], [[grey hair|grey]] to [[white hair]] tied into a [[ponytail]] and [[brown eyes]]. She wears a black [[pleated skirt]], a black [[jacket]] [[off shoulder|off the shoulder]], a [[thigh strap]] and a [[rabbit hair ornament]].

A cheerful girl, Five-SeveN's quotes show a deep affection towards the [[Commander (girls' frontline)|]], such as asking for a hug at the end of a logistics mission, or asking if the Commander missed her when logging in.

title: kar98k_(girls'_frontline)
body:
An android representing the [[mauser 98|Mauser Kar98K]] bolt-action [[rifle]] in [[Girls' Frontline]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[white hair]], [[pink eyes]], and wears a [[black hat]] with the [[Iron Cross]], [[black skirt]], a large [[jacket on shoulders|coat over her shoulders]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[thigh boots|thigh]] [[boots]]. Infamously, her official art portrays her with a comically [[oversized object|oversized]] Kar98k, which has led to some fanart depicting her as quite small. 

Her portrait is used as the game's app icon, and she features with [[Lee-Enfield (girls' frontline)|]] in the initial loading screen. Despite this focus in early promotional material, her illustrator [[Samail]] did not contribute much for her for years due to outside factors. Would receive a [[Kar98K (MOD3) (girls' frontline)|Neural Upgrade]].

title: agent_(girls'_frontline)
body:
First [[Sangvis Ferri]] android seen in [[Girls' Frontline]].

Holding a high position as all combat units are obedient to her commands. She is a master of both combat and command, capable of strategic coordination.

Serene and indifferent, she speaks and acts in a tidy manner. Her language is always respectful even towards her enemy, but she will give harsh titles to anyone other than her master, especially to Griffin & Kryuger.

Agent has [[grey eyes]], [[asymmetrical hair|asymmetrical]] [[black hair]] put up in large [[double bun]]s, and short black [[horns]]. There is a device on her back with a [[cable]] extending from it that plugs into an external [[collar]]. Her armament, hidden beneath a long [[dress]], consists of four boxy [[gun]] barrels on [[mechanical arms]] connected to her hips and legs on the thighs.

She wears a [[maid]] uniform that consists of a [[white shirt]] with [[puffy short sleeves]] underneath a long [[black dress]] with [[frilled dress|frilled trim]], [[black gloves]], a [[maid headdress]], [[black panties]], a black [[garter belt]], [[black thighhighs]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[high heel boots]] that go either to the [[thigh boots|thigh]] or the [[knee boots|knee]], depending on the artist.

h4. Appearance

* !post #3511503: Default
* !post #4535832: 5* Protocol Assimilation

h4. See also

* [[List of Girls' Frontline characters]]

h4. External links

* "IOP Wiki: Agent":[https://iopwiki.com/wiki/Agent]
other_names: エージェント(ドールズフロントライン)

title: 9a-91_(girls'_frontline)
body:
An android representing the [[9A-91]] rifle in [[Girls' Frontline]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[silver hair]], tied into [[low twintails]]. She has [[blue eyes]] and wears a [[blue dress]] with a [[see-through clothes|see-through]] front, exposing her [[navel]] and [[black panties|panties]]. She also wears a red [[scarf]], red [[beret]] and black [[thighhighs]]. She dons a red [[star hair ornament]] in her standard skin, a likely nod to her USSR origins.

Being designed around a suppressed weapon, 9A-91 is depicted as speaking rather softly. Many of her voice lines show her constantly seeking the [[Commander (girls' frontline)|]]'s attention and approval. In her OATH lines, she outright confirms this to be her one desire. She seems to be on friendly terms with [[AS Val (girls' frontline)|]] and [[AK-74U (girls' frontline)|]].

She is voiced by [[Nakahara Mai]].

title: mdr_(girls'_frontline)
body:
A T-Doll (android) that is armed with (and thus representing) the [[Desert Tech MDR]], the "Micro Dynamic Rifle", in [[Girls' Frontline]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[grey hair]] with a [[one side up]], atop which she wears a [[beret]]. MDR has [[heterochromia]]. Like most T-Doll characters, she is seen wearing [[tactical clothes]], paired with a [[backpack]]. She also wears [[gloves]] and [[black pantyhose]].

Her official artwork shows her carrying a [[flip phone|mobile phone]], and she's often characterized as a massive shitposter with an online following. In the prequel spin-off game, [[Girls' Frontline Neural Cloud|Neural Cloud]], MDR appears as [[Kuro (neural cloud)|]].

An [[original|original character]] by [[cccpo]]. Her name is Hayakawa Mutsuki (早川睦月).

She is a [[tomboy]] with [[brown eyes]], [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]] with [[bangs]], and [[large breasts]].

She has been seen wearing a [[black one-piece swimsuit|black]] [[one-piece swimsuit|one-piece]] [[swimsuit]], and/or a [[school uniform]] consisting of a [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt|collared]] [[shirt]] and a [[black skirt|black]] [[pleated skirt|pleated]] [[skirt]].

title: junkou_no_hanmegami
body:
(じゅんこうのはんめがみ)

A two volume light novel series written by "Arai Enji":[http://araiengine.sblo.jp/] and illustrated by [[Branch (blackrabbits)|]].

title: soviet_army
body:
The [b]Workers' and Peasants' Red Army[/b], or more known by their shortened name Red Army, was the prime land warfare forces of the [[soviet|Union of Soviet Socialist Republic]]. It was established in 1917 and was in service until 1946 when the army took the official name of "Soviet Army", It was then in service until its dissolution in 1991 following the dissolution of the Soviet Union. The remaining bulk of the military would be integrated into the Russian Armed Forces.

h4.See also
* [[World War II]]
* [[Cold War]]
* [[VDV]]
* [[Soviet Border Troops]]
* [[Soviet Navy]]
* [[Soviet Air Force]]
* [[Soviet Militsiya]]
* Wiki articles: "Workers' and Peasants' Red Army":[http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_Army] & "Soviet Army":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soviet_Army

title: score
body:
A tally system that counts points in numbers. It can be used to decide the winner of a competition (games, sports, etc.) or a single counter that decides the final result one got in something (exams, single-player game, etc.).

Applicable to both real life and video game examples. The numbers must be clearly seen to represent points the player(s) achieve during a play, and it's still ongoing.

See [[musical staff]] or [[sheet music]] for music scores.

h4. See also

* [[ranking]] - The final result of a score, can be represented with numbers or letters.

title: musical_staff
body:
A set of five horizontal lines and four spaces that each represent a different musical pitch or, in the case of a percussion staff, different percussion instruments. Appropriate [[musical note]]s, depending upon the intended effect, are placed on the staff according to their corresponding pitch or function. Musical notes are placed by pitch, percussion notes are placed by instrument, and rests and other symbols are placed by convention.

When on paper, this is tagged as [[sheet music]].

h4. Examples

* !asset #24648632: Staff with [[treble clef]]

h4. See also

* [[sheet music]]
* [[musical note]]
* [[musical staff print]]
* [[Tag Group:Symbols]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Staff (music)":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Staff_(music)

title: no._21:_xxi_(solar_frost)_(pgr)
body:
An [[official alternate costume|alternate coating]] of [[No. 21 (pgr)|]]'s [[no. 21: xxi (pgr)|XXI frame]].

The Solar Frost coating retains her [[unkempt]] [[very long hair|very long]] [[white hair]], with features such as [[long bangs]], [[hair intakes]] and a strand of [[ahoge]], [[low twintails]] tied by two mechanical components. Both of her [[grey eyes]] are visible, but her skin complexion is still [[pale skin|pale]]. Featuring two [[tattoo]]s on her body, a [[text tattoo|text]] and [[barcode tattoo]] on the back of her left shoulder ([[back tattoo]]), a [[musical staff]] and [[musical note]]s tattoo on her right thigh ([[leg tattoo]]). Two [[starfish]] are attached on her left thigh. Her toenails are [[toenail polish|painted]] [[orange nails|orange]].

Her [[swimsuit]] is a [[black one-piece swimsuit|black]] [[casual one-piece swimsuit]] with a [[backless swimsuit|backless design]]. Suspended to a [[frills|frilled]] [[black choker]] with a single strap on the front, and two strings to a single strap at the back, and a [[bowtie]] on the front. Other apparel elements include: [[very long sleeves|very long]] [[detached sleeves]], [[sunglasses]] [[eyewear on head|on her head]], a single [[fishnet socks|fishnet sock]] on her left foot, and low heeled [[sandals]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #6815455

title: signet_of_gold
body: A symbol used in the Elysian Realm mode of [[Honkai_Impact_3rd|Honkai Impact 3rd]], associated with [[Eden_(honkai_impact)|Eden]]. It depicts a [[coin]] embossed with a [[chalice]] design, shown amidst [[musical staff|score lines]] and various [[musical_note|musical notes]].

title: musical_note
body:
Used when a character is [[singing]] or carefree. Can also be used to cover musical notes in the background or on objects.  Covers all musical notation symbols beyond just notes.

h4. Tagged notes (beamed, rest and dotted)
* [[whole note]] (𝅝)
** [[whole rest]] (𝄻)
* [[half note]] (𝅗𝅥)
** [[half rest]] (𝄼)
** [[dotted half note]]
* [[quarter note]] (♩)
** [[quarter rest]] (𝄽)
** [[dotted quarter note]]
* [[eighth note]] (♪)
** [[beamed eighth notes]] (♫)
** [[eighth rest]] (𝄾)
** [[dotted eighth note]]
* [[sixteenth note]] (𝅘𝅥𝅯)
** [[beamed sixteenth notes]] (♬)
** [[sixteenth rest]] (𝄿)
** [[dotted sixteenth note]]
* [[thirty-second note]]
** [[beamed thirty-second notes]]
** [[thirty-second rest]]
** [[dotted thirty-second note]]
* [[sixty-fourth note]]
** [[beamed sixty-fourth notes]] (two or more 64th notes)
* [[ghost note]] (a note of any length with no discernable pitch)
* [[grace note]] 

[b]Although there are notes beyond the 64th note, it isn't necessary to tag them here.[/b]

h4. Tagged other musical notation

h6.Accidentals

* [[double flat sign]] (two semitones lower pitch)
* [[natural sign]] (♮, cancels previous accidental)

h6.Articulation marks

* [[segno sign]]
